Hyderabad Properties Rates & Trends
In Q1 2025 (Jan-March), Hyderabad’s residential real estate market continued its upward momentum, property prices saw a marginal growth of 1.8%. With infrastructure projects enhancing key areas and housing demand continuing to outstrip supply, Hyderabad’s real estate market is set for sustained growth.

As the city’s appeal strengthens, further price appreciation is likely, positioning Hyderabad as a prime destination for residential investment in the coming months.

Best Places to Buy a Flat in Hyderabad

Property prices in Hyderabad have been constantly rising in the last few years. It is not surprising since the city is exploding with foreign investments, foreign brands, MNCs, and IT companies. With the lockdown over and employees back in their workplaces, there is a huge demand for flats with good amenities. Since very few flats are showing vacancies, builders are in a rush to plan and deliver new projects.

Below are the fastest-growing localities where you can look to buy or invest in a flat in Hyderabad -

1 - Kondapur

A suburban area in western Hyderabad, Kondapur is rapidly developing, thanks to its proximity to the city’s commercial hub. The strategic location, futuristic infrastructure and connectivity of this place have all made Kondapur a lucrative market for real estate. Many prominent builders are offering modern and spacious flats at affordable prices. Taking the amenities available and the quality of life here, buying flats in Kondapur is a great investment option.

2 - Gachibowli

Included among the upcoming posh localities of Hyderabad, Gachibowli is the residential target for most IT professionals. Its proximity to the IT hubs is complemented by the shopping complexes, malls, eateries and pubs in this locality. This lively locality is home to some of the best sports establishments. Enjoy excellent accessibility along with various civic amenities to offer you an elevated standard of living. Gachibowli boasts of premium as well as reasonably-priced flats to meet the rising demand.

4 - Bachupally

On the western side of Hyderabad, Bachupally is the fastest-growing residential area. Well-connected to the rest of the city, this area is easily accessible from the IT hubs. Even during the pandemic, this area saw a huge demand. Bachupally flaunts various branded schools, educational institutions, hospitals and industries. Metro station, MMTS railway station and excellent roads add to the charm of this locality. Well-planned infrastructure, water supply and drainage systems are some of the advantages of this place.

About Hyderabad

Hyderabad, the historical dynamic city of India, still remains in focus for its vibrant growth. The city blends modern infrastructure smoothly with ancient architecture which is a big draw for the tourism industry. The already developed business foundation due to large MNCs and IT companies, is reaping the benefit now with higher foreign and local investments. New job opportunities, better urban facilities and implementation of government projects have given a boost to the real estate market.

The capital value of resid...Read moreential properties is seeing an upswing while vacancy rates are going down. This is a great time to invest in flats in Hyderabad. With a rise of about 75% in the sale of flats during last year, builders are making a beeline to launch numerous projects in the city. Hyderabad is also an investment-friendly city. Not only the IT hubs but also numerous start-ups have made Hyderabad their head office. Add to that the road development projects and metro rail projects contributing to smooth connectivity. Wherever you buy a flat in Hyderabad, you are going to be well-connected to the rest of the city.

Hyderabad Real Estate Market

A thriving IT sector and excellent infrastructure drive Hyderabad’s real estate market. Ongoing infrastructure transformations in Hyderabad’s key areas helps sustain the city’s sustained growth in real estate. Various flats in Hyderabad for sale come with many facilities and services, giving you hassle-free, comfortable living.

In Q1 2025 (Jan-March), Hyderabad’s property market remained attractive to both end-users and investors. Demand increased by 7.5% quarter-on-quarter (QoQ), supply also grew by 4.1% QoQ; despite this, the property rates in Hyderabad increased marginally by 1.8%.

Flats in Hyderabad (1/2/3/3+ BHK apartments) are priced in the range of Rs 8,300 to Rs 10,200 per sqft. The average rate of multistorey apartments in Hyderabad is Rs 7,000 per sqft and builder floors are priced at Rs 6,100 per sqft. Homebuyers in Hyderabad preferred 3 BHK mid-range properties, with a whopping 68% of the demand s...Read morehare and 52% of the supply share. On the other hand, 2 BHK units account for a more modest 27% demand share.

An analysis of quarterly variations showed increased rates (Rs/sqft). For instance, the highest growth price on a QoQ basis was found for 2 BHK apartment. It increased from 5.1% in Q4 2024 to 21.3% in Q1 2025.

Some of the top projects of Q1 2025 in Hyderabad include Cybercity Oriana, The Regent, Aparna Sarovar Zicon, Srinidhis Indraprastha Residency, The Legacey by Ananda Homes, My Home Tridasa, Indis Viva City, Sahasram The Ananda, Aakriti Cyan and DSR Park Ridge.

According to the number of top localities searched on MagicBricks in the first quarter of 2025, the northern and western parts of Hyderabad remained highly attractive for homebuyers. This is due to their excellent connectivity with the rest of the city via Nehru Outer Ring Road (ORR).

In the first quarter of 2025, Gachibowli emerged as the most sought-after micro-market in terms of demand. The average property rate in Gachibowli is Rs 10,300 per sqft. Meanwhile, Kondapur and Moosapet remained among the top three micro-markets in demand.
